Results.ReviewText: This is the one I always have even though it's instant coffee you would never know by the taste, when made it smells and tastes of quality and the first burst of the seal on a jar reminds me of a coffee house, a quality coffee and with change still in my purse
Results.Title: Liquid refreshment

Results.ReviewText: Quick, easy, convenient ... but price wise  light on the purse.  I read somewhere years ago, that instant coffee had health benifits over other coffees, so it was a conscience decision to drink but ....I really look forward to my first Nescafé in the morning.
Results.Title: Bought Nescafé for over 30 years

Results.ReviewText: Yes it's a nice colour and the aroma is very familiar, but that's the problem. Among the more intense and unusual instant coffees, this is the one that feels like it's had too many repeats. Sorry nescafe red - you're sending me snoozing when I need waking up.
Results.Title: The uninspiring one

Results.ReviewText:
Come the morning first thing I want is a good cup of coffee - without waiting for a coffee maker to splutter and gurgle for mintues - that is where Nescafe Original come out first.
Good coffee - relaible and consistent - made as quick as the kettle can boil;
Results.Title: Easy for the Morning

Results.ReviewText: I normally drink either a more expensive brand or filter coffee, but you know youre getting a decent cup of instant coffee with this. I have small jar in my van and often buy this when I am on holiday, as it is an oasis of reliability on a shelf of unknowns!
Results.Title: Reliable, especially when abroad

Results.ReviewText: I have always bought Nescafe and also buy it for my art class as I am in charge of the coffee and teas.  Everyone always says they really enjoy the coffee and that it really tastes great.  My tip is a good spoonful in each cup really brings out the flavour.
Results.Title: Tasted Great

Results.ReviewText: Been buying Nescafé original for more years than I care to remember,but I do remember never having been let down by Nescafé original,and having tried various other brands via free samples,at friends etc,I've never found a coffee that comes close to Nescafé.
Results.Title: Always 100% quality

Results.ReviewText:
I have travelled all over the world and every country knows and serves Nescafé so why would I not reward myself with the satisfying and rewarding taste of Nescafé original.
The flavour and quality never let you down and the price is always value for money
Results.Title: Simply the Best

Results.ReviewText:
Have used this brand of coffee for as long as I can remember, never disappoints and never bitter like some brands.
Even better value for money with the 150g refill pack and better for environment.
Have tried other brands but always come back to this one.
Results.Title: Great tasting coffee

Results.ReviewText: I've been using an own label coffee but they'd run out, so I bought Nescafe Original Blend instead. I'm so glad I did! It tastes just like percolated coffee. Now that I've tried it I'll not be going back to the own label variety-Nescafe is so much better.
Results.Title: REAL coffee!

Results.ReviewText:
I always buy Nescafé Classic. I have tried other coffees but they just don't come anywhere near. One of my favourite pleasures in life is to break the foil on a new jar and smell the wonderful aroma.
Deprive me of  Nescafé and it's grounds for divorce!!
Results.Title: My Number One Choice!

Results.ReviewText: Such a smooth coffee with a clear and crisp taste. Can make 50 cups for the price of a large latte from the big coffee shops - and to me it tastes just as good with no after taste without he few hundred calories - and i can make it just how i like it!!!
Results.Title: Smooth and Rich

Results.ReviewText: the new red top is a step backwards. The wholesome flavour that I enjoyed has disappeared and I am seriously considering to change to another brand which will have the flavour'  The best advice  I can give is to change it back to what we are accustomed.
Results.Title: somebody made a mistake

Results.ReviewText: I've been drinking this for some time now and really look forward to each cup of this exquisite blend. I love the aroma, satisfying taste and sense of relaxation it brings. I would thoroughly recommend it to anyone who really wants to savour the moment.
Results.Title: Great Taste

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe is the only coffee that is worth drinking. I have tried many others and they dont give you that same satisfying feeling. Pure luxury. I was brought up on nescafe and its all i have, i drink it black so i definetly get the best out of the taste.
Results.Title: Pure Luxury

Results.ReviewText: I do enjoy nescafe original. I've drank it for years now. Although I did prefer the normal one not this new double filtered 1 . I thought the older 1 tasted so much nicer. I buy it every week.  But only when the big jar is on offer for £5 at morrisons.
Results.Title: Nescafe

Results.ReviewText: It doesn't taste the same as the brown topped coffee. Have reverted back to Nescafé Gold which is a little more expensive but preferable to the new red topped Nescafé. I even take my instant coffee when I go abroad as I tend not to like local brands!!
Results.Title: Not over keen

Results.ReviewText: Great first thing in the morning gives you that get up and go, keeps me going through a 12 hour shift, and it's nice to get home after work and enjoy a nice Nescafé in the garden. And to end the day a nice frothy Nescafé made with milk for a night cap
Results.Title: Great taste

Results.ReviewText: I've been buying this for years why because of the great taste, why do you think .If it wasn't consistantly great I wouldn't buy it thats why I've been a loyal customer, and would recommrend it to anyone you can trust the taste nad it smells good to.
Results.Title: Great Taste

Results.ReviewText: I would highly recommend nescafe original, for me it has the best taste of instant coffee comparable to others on the market.  I have tried various other brands over the years but always go back to nescafe for the consistent and high quality product!
Results.Title: Consistently good

Results.ReviewText: This is a great inexpensive coffee for coffee lovers who need more than one cup a day as it tastes great but doesn't cost as much as other coffee's, but it tastes expensive!! Really nice if you make it with hot milk, better than those coffee houses!
Results.Title: Great everyday more than once a day coffee!

Results.ReviewText: Good instant coffee but as with all instants missing the nuances of the real thing worth a buy as better than most of its competitors and because it contains caffeine is actually good for you. Caffeine being a good antioxidant and neural accelerator
Results.Title: decent warm brown

Results.ReviewText: I always buy Nescafé Original - it's been a staple on my shopping list.  It's an all round coffee that can't be beaten, and doesn't break the bank either.  I take mine black which makes it so simple for anybody to serve to me and still taste great.
Results.Title: Wow!

Results.ReviewText: This is my husbands favorite coffee...and now mine. The best bit is when you pierce the foil and get that Nescafé aroma that you don't get with any other coffee ☕️ love the smooth classic taste that never fails to deliver my morning coffee perk up.
Results.Title: The original

Results.ReviewText: I always buy this Nescafe original coffee for the smooth, dark, rich coffee aroma and delicious taste.  I would never buy anything else. Whether it's a healthy black coffee day or a creamy, warming Latte day you'll never beat that Nescafe flavour.
Results.Title: Smooth but with excellent "wake me up" power

Results.ReviewText: A strong flavoured coffee, without a bitter after taste. The refill pack is not only cost effective but kinder on the environment. Great for use in baking, my family love my Coffee and Baileys cake, and this instant original flavours it perfectly.
Results.Title: Great tasting coffee

Results.ReviewText: I buy this item to make my milky coffee with first thing in the morning. Without my Milky Nescafe Coffee I can not function. I even take a bottle with me when I go on holiday to ensure I get that same delicious flavour no matter where I might be.
Results.Title: Excellent Flavour

Results.ReviewText: Love the smell of Nescafe but can't stand the stuff myself! Although the wife drinks it by the bucket load and it keeps her going all day long. I don't know how she sleeps at night, although it probably helps running a house with 4 young kids....
Results.Title: Keeps the wife charged up.
